1. Preheat the oven to 180 degrees. 2. Mix the butter and harissa in a tray and add the cubed beets and leek. Mix everything together to coat. Roast for 25-30 minutes. 3. Meanwhile, place the bulgur wheat in a suitable container. Add boiling water and place the lid on tightly. Leave to soak for 10 minutes, then fluff the bulgur wheat with a fork to separate the grains. 4. Add the bulgur to the vegetables, along with the coriander. Mix well to combine. Scatter the pumpkin seeds and feta on top before serving.